# ── Environment / Secrets ────────────────────────────────────
# Never commit real API keys — keep them in firebase-config.js
# only after adding that file to .gitignore if keys are sensitive,
# OR use environment variable injection via a build tool.
# For a fully static site using Firebase JS SDK (public keys),
# committing firebase-config.js is acceptable per Google's guidance.
# Reference: https://firebase.google.com/docs/projects/api-keys

